title: Wuhan Jianghan University F.C.
text:
Wuhan Jianghan University F.C. (<a href="Simplified%20Chinese%20characters">Chinese</a>: 武汉江汉大学足球俱乐部) is a Chinese professional <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club located in <a href="Wuhan">Wuhan</a>. They compete in the <a href="Chinese%20Women%27s%20Super%20League">Chinese Women's Super League</a>, and their home stadium is Tazihu Football Training Centre.
History.
Wuhan Jianghan University F.C. was founded in 2001 as a cooperation between <a href="Jianghan%20University">Jianghan University</a> and the Wuhan football association.
In 2017, the team won the first honour in its history, winning the <a href="2017%20China%20Women%27s%20League%20One">2017 China Women's League One</a> title to achieve promotion to the China Women's Super League for the first time in its history. In the <a href="2018%20Chinese%20Women%27s%20League%20season">2018 China Women's Super League</a> season, they finished fourth.
At the <a href="2019%20FIFA%20Women%27s%20World%20Cup">2019 FIFA Women's World Cup</a> they had five representatives in the China national team selected for the competition. Following the tournament, they re-signed former player <a href="Wang%20Shuang%20%28footballer%29">Wang Shuang</a> after a season at <a href="Paris%20Saint-Germain%20F%C3%A9minine">Paris Saint-Germain</a> ahead of the <a href="2019%20Chinese%20Women%27s%20League%20season">2019 China Women's Super League</a> campaign.
